The paper deals with machine learning and statistical testing, which are both broad areas of computer science. The focus on testing the assumption of exchangeability in machine learning suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of martingales and probability distributions also suggests a possible fit under cs.ST (Statistics) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the investigation of performance on benchmark datasets suggests a possible fit under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
